titles.title: Entrance to the Grand Canal, Venice

texts.textentryhtml: George Cavendish-Bentinck (1821-1891), London; Purchased by Jean Paul Richter (1847-1937) from "Cavendish Bentinck Sale," Christie, Manson & Woods, in London, England, July 11, 1891 (Lot 631[?], Canaletto, The Doge's Palace, Sketch); Purchased from him by Henry White Cannon (1850-1934) in Florence on March 10, 1906; By descent to his son, Henry (Harry) W. Cannon, Jr. (1887-1966), Class of 1910; Donated to the Museum in 1935.
